Tesla Inc. TSLA, +4.90% is acquiring computer-vision startup DeepScale, according to a report on CNBC Tuesday that cited a social-media post by a DeepScale executive and two people familiar with the deal. DeepScale's Chief Executive Forrest Iandola's said on LinkedIn that he had joined Tesla as senior machine-learning scientist, CNBC said, citing the post. The people familiar with the deal confirmed the deal, but declined to disclose terms, CNBC said. Tesla shares approached the end of the trading day 1.7% higher. The company did not immediately return a request for comment. The shares have lost 26% this year, contrasting with gains of 17% for the S&P 500 index. SPX, +0.17%